# Project context

This repo is the **Task 2 Рђћ Operator Dashboard** for the agriQ take-home: a **React SPA** with **mock data only** (no backend in scope for Task 2).

## Stack

- **React 19**, **TypeScript**, **Vite**, **react-router-dom**
- **Tailwind CSS v4** via `@tailwindcss/vite` Рђћ styling is utility-first; avoid new global CSS except `src/index.css` (tokens, `@theme`, dark variant).

## Source layout (do not flatten without reason)

| Area | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/types/` | Shared types (`PileMock`, `SensorReading`, `OperatorAlert`, `ThemePreference`, Рђд). **No runtime code.** |
| `src/data/` | Mock data and pure accessors (`getPiles`, `getPileById`, `getActiveAlerts`). Imports types from `src/types`. |
| `src/pages/` | Route-level screens (`SitesPage`, `AlertsPage`). Compose UI; keep business rules in data layer or shared helpers. |
| `src/components/` | Reusable UI (e.g. `ThemeSelect`). Prefer small, focused components. |
| `src/theme/` | Theme preference, context, `localStorage`, sync with `document.documentElement`. |

## Principles

- **Operators first**: copy and layout should work for non-technical grain storage staff (clear labels, actionable alerts).
- **Single source of truth**: pile/sensor/alert shapes live in `src/types`; mock values and derived lists live in `src/data`.
- **Prefer explicit imports** over barrel abuse; `src/types/index.ts` is the public type entry for cross-feature reuse.
